        "TradeItemDescriptionInformation": {
          "AdditionalTradeItemDescription": [
            {
              "LanguageCode": "en",
              "Value": "Product device description:\n\tThe Lingua-Fix® is a device comprised of four components which together create a saliva ejector that is used during dental procedures. \n\nThe components consist of an angle tube and a chin rest; both made of polypropylene.  A tube which is made of polyethylene.  And a piece of gauze made of a Polyester/Polyethylene based non-woven fabric. \n\nIntended use of the product:\t\nThe Lingua-Fix® is a device used for low volume evacuation of fluids from the oral cavity, during dental procedures in which sterile devices are not required. (Lingua-Fix® is not a sterile device). It is connected to a saliva ejector valve, which is used in conjunction with low volume evacuation systems. The large surface area of the suction (covered by the gauze) also protects the patients tongue during the procedure and assists in keeping the working area dry. "
            }
          ],
